ium|Helsingin olympiastadion]], Helsinki, Finland\n|{{fb|Finland}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''1'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |2\u20130\n|[[UEFA Euro 2004 Qualifying|UEFA Euro 2004 qualification]]\n|-\n|7.\n|13 October 2004\n|[[Stadio Ennio Tardini]], [[Parma]], Italy\n|{{fb|Belarus}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''1'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |4\u20133\n|[[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2006 FIFA World Cup Qualification]]\n|-\n|8.\n|13 October 2004\n|[[Stadio Ennio Tardini]], [[Parma]], Italy\n|{{fb|Belarus}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''3'''&nbsp;\u2013 1\n|align=\"center\" |4\u20133\n|[[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2006 FIFA World Cup Qualification]]\n|-\n|9.\n|26 June 2006\n|[[Fritz Walter Stadion]], [[Kaiserslautern]], Germany\n|{{fb|Australia}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''1'''&nbsp;\u2013 0\n|align=\"center\" |1\u20130\n|[[2006 FIFA World Cup]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Roma'''<ref name=SW>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/francesco-totti/92/|title=F. Totti|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=18 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Serie A]]: [[2000\u201301 Serie A|2000\u201301]]\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[2006\u201307 Coppa Italia|2006\u201307]], [[2007\u201308 Coppa Italia|2007\u201308]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[2001 Supercoppa Italiana|2001]], [[2007 Supercoppa Italiana|2007]]\n\n'''Italy'''<ref name=SW/>\n*[[FIFA World Cup]]: [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]]\n\n'''Italy Youth'''\n*[[Mediterranean Games|Mediterranean Games (Under-23)]]: [[1997 Mediterranean Games|1997]]\n*[[UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship|UEFA European Under-21 Championship]]: [[1996 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship|1996]]\n\n'''Individual'''\n<!--LEAGUE AND FEDERATION-SANCTIONED AWARDS ONLY. No fan or magazine-voted awards. Listed in chronological order from last time won.-->\n*[[Guerin d'Oro]]: 1998, 2004<ref name=\"Guerin d'Oro\"/>\n*[[Serie A Young Footballer of the Year]]: 1999<ref name=\"OscarAIC\">{{cite web|url=http://www.storiedicalcio.altervista.org/storia-assocalciatori-sergio-campana_6.html|title=L'Associazione Italiana Calciatori (AIC): La Storia|publisher=Storie di Calcio|language=Italian|accessdate=25 November 2016}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Euro 2000 Final]]: Man of the Match<ref name=\"tattered international reputation\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2006/jul/10/worldcup2006.sport2|title=Totti fails the final test and leaves a tattered international reputation|work=The Guardian|first=Jon|last=Brodkin|date=10 July 2006|accessdate=18 February 2017}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA Euro 2000]]: [[2000 UEFA European Football Championship#Awards|Team of the Tournament]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/history/memories/newsid=1627525.html|title=UEFA Euro 2000 team of the tournament|publisher=UEFA|date=1 January 2011|accessdate=31 March 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Serie A Footballer of the Year]]: 2000, 2003<ref name=\"Guerin d'Oro\"/>\n*[[Serie A Italian Footballer of the Year]]: 2000, 2001, 2003, 2004, 2007<ref name=\"Oscar-del-Calcio\"/>\n*[[European Sports Media#ESM Team of the Year|ESM Team of the Year]]: [[European Sports Media#2000.E2.80.9301|2000\u201301]], [[European Sports Media#2003.E2.80.9304|2003\u201304]], [[European Sports Media#2006.E2.80.9307|2006\u201307]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/esm-xi.html |title=ESM XI |website=RSSSF |first=Karel |last=Stokkermans |date=14 March 2007 |accessdate=29 November 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160207144925/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/esm-xi.html |archivedate=7 February 2016 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n*[[FIFA 100]]<ref name=\"Pele\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/3533891.stm|title=Pele's list of the greatest|work=BBC Sport|date=4 March 2004|accessdate=15 June 2013}}</ref>\n*[[Oscar del Calcio#Serie A Goal of the Year|Serie A Goal of the Year]]: 2005, 2006<ref name=\"Oscar-del-Calcio\"/>\n*[[2006 FIFA World Cup]] [[2006 FIFA World Cup#All-star team|All-Star Team]]'''<ref name=\"France, Italy dominate World Cup all-star squad\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/france-italy-dominate-world-cup-all-star-squad-1.572395|title=France, Italy dominate World Cup all-star squad|publisher=CBC Sports|date=7 July 2006|accessdate=27 May 2015}}</ref>\n*[[2006 FIFA World Cup]]: [[2006 FIFA World Cup#Assists|Assist Leader]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccer-europe.com/Archives/WorldCup/WorldCup2006/GoalsandAssists.html|title=2006 FIFA World Cup Goals & Assists|publisher=Soccer-Europe|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Serie A]] Assist Leader: [[1998\u201399 Serie A|1998\u201399]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.football-lineups.com/tourn/Serie_A_1998-1999/stats/top_goal_scorers/|title=Serie A 1998/99 Stats|publisher=Football-Lineups.com|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref> [[2006\u201307 Serie A|2006\u201307]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/italian-serie-a/12/statistics/assists?season=2006|title=Serie A Statistics&nbsp;\u2013 ESPN FC&nbsp;\u2013 Top Assists 2006\u201307|publisher=ESPN FC|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>, [[2013\u201314 Serie A#Top assists|2013\u201314]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/italian-serie-a/12/statistics/assists?season=2013|title=Serie A Statistics&nbsp;\u2013 ESPN FC&nbsp;\u2013 Top Assists 2013\u201314|publisher=ESPN FC|accessdate=30 July 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Capocannonieri|Serie A Top Scorer]]: [[2006\u201307 Serie A#Top goalscorers|2006\u201307]]<ref name=\"Serie A Top Scorers\"/>\n*[[European Golden Shoe]]: 2006\u201307<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/gboot.html|title=Golden Boot (\"Soulier d'Or\") Awards|website=RSSSF|first1=Sorin|last1=Arotaritei|first2=Roberto|last2=Di Maggio|first3=Karel|last3=Stokkermans|date=20 November 2014|accessdate=29 November 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Oscar del Calcio#Serie A Goalscorer of the Year|Oscar AIC-Serie A Top scorer]]: 2007<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/SerieA/Primo_Piano/2008/01_Gennaio/28/oscar.shtml|title=Oscar Assocalciatori Kak\u00e0 miglior giocatore|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=28 January 2008|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Pallone d'Argento]]: 2007\u201308<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ussi.it/2016/a-florenzi-il-pallone-dargento-coppa-giaime-fiumano/|title=A Florenzi il \"Pallone d'Argento\" Coppa Giaim\u00e8 Fiumano|publisher=Unione stampa sportiva italiana|language=Italian|date=8 May 2016|accessdate=18 May 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Golden Foot]]: 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldenfoot.com/winner-details.php?l=en&WinnerID=5&Title=francesco-totti|title=Francesco Totti|publisher=Golden Foot|date=11 October 2010|accessdate=29 November 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208135525/http://www.goldenfoot.com/winner-details.php?l=en&WinnerID=5&Title=francesco-totti|archivedate=8 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Premio Nazionale Carriera Esemplare \"Gaetano Scirea\"]]: 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nordmilano24.it/2014/07/25/memorial-scirea-totti-vince-premio-carriera-esemplare/|title=Memorial Scirea: Totti vince il premio \"carriera esemplare\"|publisher=Nordmilano24|language=Italian|accessdate=20 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Premio internazionale Giacinto Facchetti]]: 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/sport/calcio/2014/11/05/il-premio-facchetti-assegnato-a-totti_7904a702-17db-491b-95b3-5d684d28ff59.html|title=Il premio Facchetti assegnato a Totti|work=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|date=5 November 2014|accessdate=20 January 2015}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] All-time XI: 2015<ref name=\"UEFA\"/>\n*[[A.S. Roma|Roma]] [[A.S. Roma#Hall of Fame|Hall of Fame]]: Class of 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asroma.com/en/news/2017/5/as-roma-induct-totti-into-hall-of-fame|title=AS Roma induct Totti into Hall of Fame|publisher=AS Roma|date=29 May 2017|accessdate=31 July 2017}}</ref>\n*[[UEFA President's Award]]: 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.org/about-uefa/president/news/newsid=2474521.html|title=Francesco Totti to receive UEFA President's Award|publisher=UEFA|date=1 June 2017|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"UEFA President's Award\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=2050865.html|title=UEFA President's Award|publisher=UEFA.com|date=2 January 2014|accessdate=1 June 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Gazzetta Sports Awards]] Legend: 2017<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/12-12-2017/gazzetta-sports-awards-buffon-uomo-anno-totti-contador-leggende-240179017831.shtml|title=Gazzetta Sports Awards: Buffon l'uomo dell'anno, Totti e Contador leggende|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=12 December 2017|accessdate=12 January 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Globe Soccer Awards|Globe Soccer]] Player Career Award: 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.globesoccer.com/winners/francesco-totti-career-award/|title=Globe Soccer Awards: Francesco Totti (Career Award)|publisher=Globe Soccer|date=28 December 2017|accessdate=29 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[Laureus World Sports Awards#Winners by year|Laureus Academy World Sports Exceptional Achievement Award]]: 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/tennis/news/12110/11270150/roger-federer-wins-sportsman-and-comeback-of-the-year-at-laureus-awards|title=Roger Federer wins Sportsman and Comeback of the Year at Laureus Awards|publisher=Sky Sports|author1=Nicholas Wright|date=27 February 2018|accessdate=27 February 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Gran Gal\u00e0 del Calcio|Gran Gal\u00e0 del Calcio AIC]] Career Award: 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/2018/12/totti-receives-career-award-at-gran-gala-del-calcio|title=TOTTI RECEIVES CAREER AWARD AT GRAN GALA DEL CALCIO|publisher=AS Roma|date=4 December 2018|accessdate=5 February 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Italian Football Hall of Fame]]: 2018<ref name=\"2018-SerieAHoF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.figc.it/it/formazione-ed-eventi/news/totti-zanetti-e-allegri-tra-i-premiati-dell-8-edizione-della-hall-of-fame-del-calcio-italiano/|title=Totti, Zanetti e Allegri tra i premiati d